                <h1>Understanding Sources of Background Radiation</h1>
                <p>Background radiation comes from natural sources such as cosmic rays from outer space, terrestrial radiation from the Earth's crust, and radon gas emissions from soil and rocks. Additionally, human-made sources like medical procedures, nuclear power plants, and fallout from nuclear tests contribute to the overall exposure. Understanding these sources helps assess risk.</p>
